defs.docs:
Small vectors in various sizes. These store a certain number of elements inline, and fall back
 to the heap for larger allocations.  This can be a useful optimization for improving cache
 locality and reducing allocator traffic for workloads that fit within the inline buffer.

defs.name: ExtendFromSlice
defs.docs: Trait to be implemented by a collection that can be extended from a slice

defs.name: extend_from_slice
defs.docs: Extends a collection from a slice of its element type

defs.name: CapacityOverflow
defs.docs: Overflow `usize::MAX` or other error during size computation

defs.name: AllocErr
defs.docs: The allocator return an error

defs.name: CollectionAllocErr
defs.docs: Error type for APIs with fallible heap allocation

defs.name: Drain
defs.docs: An iterator that removes the items from a `SmallVec` and yields them by value.

defs.name: SmallVec
defs.docs: A `Vec`-like container that can store a small number of elements inline.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Construct an empty vector

defs.name: with_capacity
defs.docs:
Construct an empty vector with enough capacity pre-allocated to store at least `n`
 elements.

defs.name: from_vec
defs.docs: Construct a new `SmallVec` from a `Vec<A::Item>`.

defs.name: from_buf
defs.docs:
Constructs a new `SmallVec` on the stack from an `A` without
 copying elements.

defs.name: from_buf_and_len
defs.docs:
Constructs a new `SmallVec` on the stack from an `A` without
 copying elements. Also sets the length, which must be less or
 equal to the size of `buf`.

defs.name: from_buf_and_len_unchecked
defs.docs:
Constructs a new `SmallVec` on the stack from an `A` without
 copying elements. Also sets the length. The user is responsible
 for ensuring that `len <= A::size()`.

defs.name: set_len
defs.docs: Sets the length of a vector.

defs.name: inline_size
defs.docs: The maximum number of elements this vector can hold inline

defs.name: len
defs.docs: The number of elements stored in the vector

defs.name: is_empty
defs.docs: Returns `true` if the vector is empty

defs.name: capacity
defs.docs: The number of items the vector can hold without reallocating

defs.name: spilled
defs.docs: Returns `true` if the data has spilled into a separate heap-allocated buffer.

defs.name: drain
defs.value: fn <R> (&mut self, range: R) -> Drain<'_, A>
defs.docs:
Creates a draining iterator that removes the specified range in the vector
 and yields the removed items.

defs.name: push
defs.docs: Append an item to the vector.

defs.name: pop
defs.docs: Remove an item from the end of the vector and return it, or None if empty.

defs.name: grow
defs.docs: Re-allocate to set the capacity to `max(new_cap, inline_size())`.

defs.name: try_grow
defs.value: fn (&mut self, new_cap: usize) -> Result<(), CollectionAllocErr>
defs.docs: Re-allocate to set the capacity to `max(new_cap, inline_size())`.

defs.name: reserve
defs.docs: Reserve capacity for `additional` more elements to be inserted.

defs.name: try_reserve
defs.value: fn (&mut self, additional: usize) -> Result<(), CollectionAllocErr>
defs.docs: Reserve capacity for `additional` more elements to be inserted.

defs.name: reserve_exact
defs.docs: Reserve the minimum capacity for `additional` more elements to be inserted.

defs.name: try_reserve_exact
defs.value: fn (&mut self, additional: usize) -> Result<(), CollectionAllocErr>
defs.docs: Reserve the minimum capacity for `additional` more elements to be inserted.

defs.name: shrink_to_fit
defs.docs: Shrink the capacity of the vector as much as possible.

defs.name: truncate
defs.docs: Shorten the vector, keeping the first `len` elements and dropping the rest.

defs.name: as_slice
defs.docs: Extracts a slice containing the entire vector.

defs.name: as_mut_slice
defs.docs: Extracts a mutable slice of the entire vector.

defs.name: swap_remove
defs.docs: Remove the element at position `index`, replacing it with the last element.

defs.name: clear
defs.docs: Remove all elements from the vector.

defs.name: remove
defs.docs:
Remove and return the element at position `index`, shifting all elements after it to the
 left.

defs.name: insert
defs.value: fn (&mut self, index: usize, element: A::Item) -> ()
defs.docs: Insert an element at position `index`, shifting all elements after it to the right.

defs.name: insert_many
defs.value: fn <I> (&mut self, index: usize, iterable: I) -> ()
defs.docs:
Insert multiple elements at position `index`, shifting all following elements toward the
 back.

defs.name: into_vec
defs.docs:
Convert a SmallVec to a Vec, without reallocating if the SmallVec has already spilled onto
 the heap.

defs.name: into_boxed_slice
defs.docs:
Converts a `SmallVec` into a `Box<[T]>` without reallocating if the `SmallVec` has already spilled
 onto the heap.

defs.name: into_inner
defs.docs: Convert the SmallVec into an `A` if possible. Otherwise return `Err(Self)`.

defs.name: retain
defs.docs: Retains only the elements specified by the predicate.

defs.name: dedup
defs.docs: Removes consecutive duplicate elements.

defs.name: dedup_by
defs.docs: Removes consecutive duplicate elements using the given equality relation.

defs.name: dedup_by_key
defs.value: fn <F, K> (&mut self, mut key: F) -> ()
defs.docs: Removes consecutive elements that map to the same key.

defs.name: from_raw_parts
defs.value: fn (ptr: *mut A::Item, length: usize, capacity: usize) -> SmallVec<A>
defs.docs:
Creates a `SmallVec` directly from the raw components of another
 `SmallVec`.

defs.name: from_slice
defs.docs: Copy the elements from a slice into a new `SmallVec`.

defs.name: insert_from_slice
defs.docs:
Copy elements from a slice into the vector at position `index`, shifting any following
 elements toward the back.

defs.name: extend_from_slice
defs.docs: Copy elements from a slice and append them to the vector.

defs.name: resize
defs.value: fn (&mut self, len: usize, value: A::Item) -> ()
defs.docs: Resizes the vector so that its length is equal to `len`.

defs.name: from_elem
IntoIter
defs.docs: An iterator that consumes a `SmallVec` and yields its items by value.

defs.name: as_slice
defs.docs: Returns the remaining items of this iterator as a slice.

defs.name: as_mut_slice
defs.docs: Returns the remaining items of this iterator as a mutable slice.

defs.name: Array
defs.docs: Types that can be used as the backing store for a SmallVec

defs.name: Item
defs.docs: The type of the array's elements.

defs.name: size
defs.docs: Returns the number of items the array can hold.

defs.name: ToSmallVec
defs.docs: Convenience trait for constructing a `SmallVec`

defs.name: to_smallvec
defs.docs: Construct a new `SmallVec` from a slice.
